Myanmar Appoints New Members of Civil Services
YANGON , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- The Myanmar State Peace and Development Council appointed four new members of the Civil Services Selection and Training Board ( CSSTB ) shortly after a major reshuffle of the government was carried out Saturday , allowing five former members of the Board to retire .
According to an official announcement made by the state-run Radio Myanmar Saturday night , the four new members appointed include U Nyunt Swe who is allowed to retire from the post as deputy minister of foreign affairs .
The CSSTB is an important organization of the government responsible for the selection and training of civil services personnel for the appointment at the government 's administrative sector .
